{
  "texts": [
    "User experienceNeuronBridge is an end-user web application designed for accessibility and ease-of-use by wet-lab biologists.",
    "Using any web browser, a user can log into the service's website with their Google account credentials or create a separate NeuronBridge account.",
    "The user is presented with a simple search interface for looking up their neuron or GAL4 driver line of interest (Fig. 3).",
    "Searching for a neuron identifier returns CDM representations of EM neuron reconstructions, in the JRC2018 Unisex alignment space.",
    "Searching for a driver line returns CDM representations of that driver line."
  ]
}